helpdesk-ticket.subject: Turn of Auto Creation of Tel/Web Codes
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello—
When we register our new students for fall (starting in late May or early June), we don’t want them to be able to change their schedule until Welcome Week. So, we need to disable the AL code step in the job that creates accounts.
I believe the job is called—Create myMSOE Accts for New Students. The myMSOE account should be created and they should be able to view things, they just shouldn’t have the Tel/Web code populated (that allows for schedule changes). This typically gets turned off around now, then Val scripts them in at the beginning of Welcome Week, and this job starts doing that step again at the beginning of Welcome Week.
So, no AL populated in the student_master.tel_web_grp_cde.
Mary
Mary Nielsen Registrar Milwaukee School of Engineering Phone: 414-277-7216 Fax: 414-277-6914 www.msoe.edu
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello—
 
When we register our new students for fall (starting in late May or early June), we don’t want them to be able to change their schedule until Welcome Week.  So, we need to disable the AL code step in the job that creates accounts.
 
I believe the job is called—Create myMSOE Accts for New Students.   The myMSOE account should be created and they should be able to view things, they just shouldn’t have the Tel/Web code populated (that allows for schedule changes).  This typically gets turned off around now, then Val scripts them in at the beginning of Welcome Week, and this job starts doing that step again at the beginning of Welcome Week.
 
So, no AL populated in the student_master.tel_web_grp_cde. 
 
Mary
 
Mary Nielsen
Registrar
Milwaukee School of  Engineering

www.msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Thomas
There is no software on computer #9 in S-340 that must be retained after the OS upgrade. It just needs to have Office and network access. We want to use this machine to test out some new software that we are going install that requires Win7. Ultimately we will build an image that will be duplicated across all the computers in S-340. We need to test things out on computer #9 first.
Thanks.
Steve W

helpdesk-note.body-html: I left a voicemail with Chase saying the same thing. I am not sure if he is actually using this number while he is there, as it went straight to voicemail.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Chase,
Can you connect to Global Protect? If you need to install Global Protect (our VPN), follow these instructions
Once you are connected to the VPN, go to Start Menu, right-click on Computer and go to Properties. Scroll down, you should see something along the lines of "Activate Windows Now", click on that.
It should activate successfully. Your background will still be black. You will need to manually change it. Or keep it. The decision is yours.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Chase,

Can you connect to Global Protect? 
If you need to install Global Protect (our VPN), follow these instructions

Once you are connected to the VPN, go to Start Menu, right-click on Computer and go to Properties.
Scroll down, you should see something along the lines of "Activate Windows Now", click on that.

It should activate successfully.
Your background will still be black. You will need to manually change it. Or keep it. The decision is yours. 

Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.description: HR is going through Jenzabar for checks and direct deposits now. Ann set up the reports, but the formatting doesn't fit with the check and direct deposit stock.

helpdesk-note.body: Reassigning to Database team.

helpdesk-note.body:
The check report is fixed, but I was unable to test the direct deposit. Tracy added information into play, but check number and 'DD' check type are not coming through. Tracy said she processed the play information just like how she would in production, so we created a ticket with Jenzabar:
In play we are running the Paychecks/Direct Deposits/Registers for batch 2530. Paper copies of paychecks are being produced, but direct deposit stubs are not being produced. When we try to customize the r_employee_direct_deposit_mse, its looking for check number; however, on the chk_hist_header_v, the check number is not filling in. We need to get this working in play so we can format the Direct Deposit Form before moving to production. Did we miss a step that would assign direct deposit check numbers in the payroll process? JZ Ticket: #350216
helpdesk-note.body-html:
The check report is fixed, but I was unable to test the direct deposit. Tracy added information into play, but check number and 'DD' check type are not coming through. Tracy said she processed the play information just like how she would in production, so we created a ticket with Jenzabar: 

In play we are running the Paychecks/Direct Deposits/Registers for batch 2530. Paper copies of paychecks are being produced, but direct deposit stubs are not being produced. When we try to customize the r_employee_direct_deposit_mse, its looking for check number; however, on the chk_hist_header_v, the check number is not filling in. We need to get this working in play so we can format the Direct Deposit Form before moving to production. Did we miss a step that would assign direct deposit check numbers in the payroll process?
JZ Ticket: #350216

helpdesk-note.body:
JZ replied: Is there a Direct Deposit Group specified on their timecard?
I sent this on to Tracy and asked her to check.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Outlook Email Password Update
helpdesk-ticket.description:
How do I update the password in the outlook app on my school pc? I changed the password this morning and it is not updated on the app.
Thanks
Sent from Outlook Mobile<https://aka.ms/blhgte>
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
How do I update the password in the outlook app on my school pc? I changed the password this morning and it is not updated on the app.
Thanks
Sent from Outlook Mobile

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Austin Calderone,
You could just follow these steps:
1. Open Credential Manager ( Control Panel < User Accounts < Credential Manager )
2. Under the generic credentials, Choose " Remove from Vault " for MS Office or MS Outlook Credentials (That uses your msoe.edu only)
3. After you are done, reopen Outlook ( Make sure you are connected to internet )
4. A Pop-Up asking for your password with come up and the enter your new password and check " Remember my credentials"
I hope this will help, or you can always call in/ come in to the helpdesk and we can help you.

After trying many things, eventually what worked was having the EAP Method set to PEAP, the Phase 2 Authentification set to MSCHAPV2. The Identity needs to specify the MSOE domain (MSOE\username), and anonymous identity left blank.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Emma was not able to connect to the MSOE wireless on her phone. After trying many things, eventually what worked was having the EAP Method set to PEAP, the Phase 2 Authentification set to MSCHAPV2. The Identity needs to specify the MSOE domain (MSOE\username), and anonymous identity left blank.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: "Send to outlook" feature of scheduler yields calendars that are off by 1 hour
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I am attempting to export my calendar from scheduler by creating a scheduling and clicking on the “send to outlook” button. When I import this generated calendar into Outlook, all of the times are off by one hour. For example, my class which is scheduled from 4:00-5:00 is importing as a 3:00 to 4:00 class.
This is a big concern, as many faculty and students use this tool to automatically generate their calendars, and it seems that there is a problem either with time zones or daylight savings resulting in this on hour shift.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Walter Schilling, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7714
Hi Dr Schilling
This is a normal error/action for this type of web server configuration. Facility web was designed to provide individual websites for faculty members that are directly linkable for the students. Nothing is placed in the index list that is at the root path https://faculty-web.msoe.edu/ and that is why you are given a directory index of no items. Thank you for your concern, please reply to this ticket if you have any questions.
I am connecting to faculty-web.msoe.edu. However, if I do not enter in a full faculty members name, I am directed to an index of /, not an error page or a main page for the server.
Dr. Walter Schilling
Associate Professor, Milwaukee School of Engineering
EECS Department
schilling@msoe.edu
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Tier 2 Staff Support Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Adding Email Account to Phone Apps
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good morning,
I am attempting to add my new MSOE email address to my iPhone email app (or the outlook app) without any luck. Is there something special that needs to be done? There are no issues logging on in a browser but both apps did not find/link to my email.
Thank you,
Jake
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Good morning,
I am attempting to add my new MSOE email address to my iPhone email app (or the outlook app) without any luck.  Is there something special that needs to be done?  There are no issues logging on in a browser but both apps did not find/link to my email.

Thank you,

Jake

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jake,
Here are some instructions to set up your email on the iPhone iOS 9 Outlook App:
1. Make sure the most recent version of the application is downloaded on your phone. 2. When no account is yet linked, an icon that says "Get Started" should appear. Touch this icon. 3. Right away it should prompt you with a screen to enter your msoe email address. make sure the format is "yourusername@msoe.edu" . 4. Tap "Add Account". You should be redirected to the MSOE single sign-on page. Enter your MSOE email again and your password. 5. After this, your account should be completely set up.
After you have tried following these directions let us know if you have a different version of the iOS operating system and can't get the newest version of Outlook.
Call, e-mail, or come into the desk if you have any questions!
Thank you! MSOE Information Technology Tier 1 Helpdesk Team Benjamin Mahon 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body-html: Email is constantly locking her out.  Its hitting her account all day and all night.  It looks like she only accesses email from school but I do see she has a Samsung device that she connected at one point, I also see that she connected via Chrome Mobile for Android in the past

helpdesk-note.body:
Sarah,
Email is the cause of your constant lock outs. A device of yours is attempting to access email all day and night. This causes the lockout. At some point you had a Samsung device connect to your email, which might have a bad password saved.
We have this guide for troubleshooting your constant lockouts.
Please go through all of your devices that you have accessed MSOE email and make sure the credentials are accurate, or delete the account / app that you used to connect. Often if this is happening you will be able to see old emails on the device, but it will not update with new emails since the password change.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Sarah,

Email is the cause of your constant lock outs. A device of yours is attempting to access email all day and night. This causes the lockout. At some point you had a Samsung device connect to your email, which might have a bad password saved. 

We have this guide for troubleshooting your constant lockouts.

Please go through all of your devices that you have accessed MSOE email and make sure the credentials are accurate, or delete the account / app that you used to connect. Often if this is happening you will be able to see old emails on the device, but it will not update with new emails since the password change. 

Have a great day!
